---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact and Corrections - The National Angle"
  description="How to contact The National Angle, send tips, and request corrections."
>
  <article class="infoPage">
    <div class="infoHero">
      <div class="signalPills"><span>Contact</span><span>Corrections</span><span>Reader trust</span></div>
      <h1>Contact and Corrections</h1>
      <p class="pageDeck">The National Angle is built to explain what sits behind the headline. Reader tips, source notes, and correction requests help keep that work sharper.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="infoGrid">
      <section><p class="cardLabel">01</p><h2>News Tips</h2><p>If you see a pattern, document, local report, public filing, or overlooked development that deserves a clearer angle, send it with as much context as possible.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">02</p><h2>Corrections</h2><p>If an article contains a factual error, missing context, or wording that could mislead readers, include the article link and the specific sentence or claim that needs review.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">03</p><h2>Transparency</h2><p>When a material correction is needed, the article should be updated clearly and the updated date should reflect the change.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">04</p><h2>Contact</h2><p>For now, use the site owner email connected to this publication account. A dedicated editorial inbox should be added before any larger public launch.</p></section>
    </div>

    <div class="infoActions"><a class="btn primary" href="/">Explore the reporting</a><a class="btn" href="/method">Read the method</a></div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
